The President's Council on Jobs and Competitiveness is holding a listening and action session in Portland, Oregon on August 31st. The session will focus on curbing America's engineering shortage, which is threatening the country's role as a leading innovator and hindering job creation. The panelists will include senior Administration officials, business leaders, and Deans from engineering schools. People can participate in the event by submitting questions and comments beforehand through the White House group on LinkedIn and the official website. The session will be live-streamed on the website and people can engage on Twitter using the hashtag #jobscouncil. These regional sessions are part of the Council's efforts to gather new voices and ideas to inform their policy recommendations. The Council's core mission is to promote growth by investing in American businesses, educating and training American workers, and attracting jobs and businesses to the United States.